   },
   "source": [
    "#### Imports\n",
    "Besides the math and plotting libraries, I'm using yellowbrick for some of its evaluation visualizations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:05.601717Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:01.580375Z"
    },
    "hidden": true,
    "pycharm": {
     "is_executing": false
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from jupyterthemes import jtplot\n",
    "# to make some plots match my notebook theme, not required\n",
    "jtplot.style()\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import QuantileTransformer\n",
    "from yellowbrick.target import BalancedBinningReference\n",
    "from yellowbrick.target import FeatureCorrelation\n",
    "from yellowbrick.classifier import ROCAUC\n",
    "from yellowbrick.classifier import ClassificationReport\n",
    "from scipy.stats import uniform\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import RandomizedSearchCV\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.feature_selection import SelectKBest, chi2\n",
    "# because SO says this makes XGBoost work, and it did\n",
    "import os\n",
    "os.environ['KMP_DUPLICATE_LIB_OK']='True'\n",
    "from xgboost import XGBClassifier\n",
    "# plot fonts\n",
    "from matplotlib import rcParams\n",
    "rcParams['font.sans-serif'] = ['Overpass', 'DejaVu Sans',\n",
    "                               'Lucida Grande', 'Verdana']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "heading_collapsed": true
   },
   "source": [
    "# The Data\n",
    "Our dataset is [housingpresident.csv](https://github.com/LLTTDAY/tf/blob/master/notebooks/housingpresident.csv), which was the output of [part one of this project](https://github.com/LLTTDAY/tf/blob/master/notebooks/Residential%20Property%20Data%20and%20Presidential%20Election%20Results%20-%20Data%20Preprocessing%20and%20Feature%20Engineering.ipynb). That notebook contains additional details on precinct geography and the various assessor tables used to make the file.  \n",
    "\n",
    "It contains about 150 features summarizing various characteristics and measurements of residential properties in each of about 2,500 voting precincts, as collected and reported by the King County Assessor's Office. The target in this database is the relative share of votes won in each precint by the Clinton or Trump campaigns."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:05.844907Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:05.607562Z"
    },
    "hidden": true,
    "pycharm": {
     "is_executing": false
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# read in the data\n",
    "data = pd.read_csv('housingpresident.csv', index_col=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# clean up some extra or missing data\n",
    "data = data.drop('Unnamed: 0',axis=1)\n",
    "data = data.dropna(subset=['trump'])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "heading_collapsed": true
   },
   "source": [
    "# The Objective\n",
    "\n",
    "The goal is to learn about how some of these features correlate with the voting preferences recorded in the precint level election results, and to determine the following: A. Whether housing data contains enough information related to voting preference that a learning model can predict an election result target variable, and B. What sort of model does that task with this data most effectively, and in the most explainable way?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-01T15:15:58.439554Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-01T15:15:58.403882Z"
    },
    "heading_collapsed": true,
    "pycharm": {
     "is_executing": false
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# Targets\n",
    "The obvious classification for an election dataset is \"won vs lost,\" or above or below .5 in our target variable. There isn't enough data to provide sufficient examples of each class with a split at a 50% vote share, so we'll use the median precinct performance as our split."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:05.884279Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:05.862773Z"
    },
    "hidden": true,
    "pycharm": {
     "is_executing": false
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# a categorical target with classes split at 50/50\n",
    "yc = (data['trump'] >= .5).astype(int)\n",
    "\n",
    "# a categorical target with classes split at the median\n",
    "yc2 = (data['trump'] > data['trump'].median()).astype(int)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "heading_collapsed": true
   },
   "source": [
    "# Examples"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:05.971108Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:05.890849Z"
    },
    "hidden": true,
    "pycharm": {
     "is_executing": false
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# make our example set by dropping the original targets and some more extra columns\n",
    "X = data.drop(['trump','trumpmed','c-AptConversion_ '], axis=1)\n",
    "dropcols = [x for x in X.columns if '_0' in x]\n",
    "X = X.drop(dropcols, axis=1)\n",
    "tcols = [x for x in X.columns if X[x].max() > 1 or X[x].min() < 0]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:06.959945Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:05.990884Z"
    },
    "hidden": true,
    "pycharm": {
     "is_executing": false
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# quantile transformation on the examples\n",
    "qt = QuantileTransformer()\n",
    "Xcols = X.columns\n",
    "X2 = pd.DataFrame(qt.fit_transform(X))\n",
    "X2.columns = X.columns"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:07.003754Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:06.983570Z"
    },
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# for manual feature selection, see below\n",
    "keeps = [\n",
    "    'r-Garage',\n",
    "    'r-YrBuilt',\n",
    "    'HUDensity'\n",
    "]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "heading_collapsed": true
   },
   "source": [
    "# Feature Selection"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "heading_collapsed": true,
    "hidden": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Feature Selection 1: SelectKBest of Chi-Squareds"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:07.068017Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:07.012723Z"
    },
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# pick a smallish number of features\n",
    "Xn = SelectKBest(chi2, k=20)\n",
    "Xnn = Xn.fit_transform(X2,yc2)\n",
    "colarray = np.array(X2.columns)[Xn.get_support()]\n",
    "Xnn = pd.DataFrame(Xnn, columns=colarray)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:07.094884Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:07.079733Z"
    },
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# make a dataframe of features and chi squared scores\n",
    "mask = Xn.get_support()\n",
    "new_features = X2.columns[mask]\n",
    "Xnscores = Xn.scores_[mask]\n",
    "features = pd.DataFrame({'feature': new_features, 'chi2': Xnscores})\n",
    "features.index = features['feature']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-09T18:28:21.932000Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-09T18:28:21.928323Z"
    },
    "heading_collapsed": true,
    "hidden": true
   },
   "source": [
    "### Chi-squared Plot"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:08.157535Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:07.111007Z"

   "outputs": [

     "data": {

     "data": {

   ],
   "source": [
    "# plot 'em\n",
    "features.sort_values(by='chi2', ascending=True).plot(kind='barh', figsize=(10,10), title='X-squared Test of Feature Correlation with Target')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:09.066385Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:08.166069Z"
    },
    "hidden": true,
    "pycharm": {
     "is_executing": false
    },
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x720 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# plot a correlation matrix\n",
    "corrmat = Xnn.corr()\n",
    "f,ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,10))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(corrmat)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "source": [
    "It's definitely the case that some of these features aren't totally independent, based on the fact that some of the measurements are relative: more of one thing means less of the other, and because of zoning laws and building codes, which often encourage or prohibit one or the other of the phenomena measured in real estate data. We will press on, though, since our goal is to see how well we can predict our target, and maybe the models can sort some of that out on their own."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Feature Selection 2: Manual"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:09.079086Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:09.070767Z"
    },
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "selected = [\n",
    "    'r-garage',\n",
    "    'r-YrBuilt',\n",
    "    'a-SectySystem_Y',\n",
    "    'c-Elevators_Y',\n",
    "    'HUDensity'\n",
    "]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:09.097824Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-10T15:14:09.083514Z"
    },
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X3 = X[selected]\n",
    "X4 = Xnn[selected]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hidden": true
   },
   "source": [

   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 134,

    "ExecuteTime": {

    },
    "hidden": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# split our data\n",
    "\n",
    "# KBest, Transformed\n",
    "X_train,X_test,y_train,y_test = train_test_split(Xnn,yc2,test_size=.2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Raw, All Features\n",
    "X1_train,X1_test,yb_train,yb_test = train_test_split(X,yc2,test_size=.2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sparse, Non-Transformed\n",
    "X3_train,X3_test,yc_train,yc_test = train_test_split(X3,yc2,test_size=.2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sparse, Transformed\n",
    "X4_train,X4_test,yd_train,yd_test = train_test_split(X4,yc2,test_size=.2)"
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",

   "metadata": {

   "source": [
    "predicts = {\n",
    "    'actual' : yc2,\n",
    "    'lrpredicted' : logreg1.predict(X),\n",
    "    'lrprob' : logreg1.predict_proba(X)[:,1],\n",
    "    'rfpredict' : rnfr.predict(X),\n",
    "    'rfprob' : rnfr.predict_proba(X)[:,1],\n",
    "    'xgpredict' : gbtr.predict(X),\n",
    "    'xgprob' : gbtr.predict_proba(X)[:,1]\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "predf = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(predicts)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 207,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2019-07-11T14:15:41.968872Z",
     "start_time": "2019-07-11T14:15:41.947623Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "predf['actual'] = np.where(predf['actual']==0, -1, 1)\n",
    "predf['lrpredicted'] = np.where(predf['lrpredicted']==0, -1, 1)\n",
    "predf['rfpredict'] = np.where(predf['rfpredict']==0, -1, 1)\n",
    "predf['xgpredict'] = np.where(predf['xgpredict']==0, -1, 1)\n",
    "predf['lrprob'] = predf['lrprob'] * predf['lrpredicted']\n",
    "predf['rfprob'] = predf['rfprob'] * predf['rfpredict']\n",
    "predf['xgprob'] = predf['xgprob'] * predf['xgpredict']"
   ]
